```json
{
  "application": "Slurm",
  "details": {
    "partition": "normal",
    "ntasks": 1,
    "memory": "1024MB",
    "output": "results/r1/hw1_%j_stdout.txt",
    "error": "results/r1/hw1_%j_stderr.txt",
    "time": "00:30:00",
    "job_name": "hw1_run4",
    "mail_user": "vishnupk@ou.edu",
    "mail_type": "ALL",
    "chdir": "/home/cs504305/deep_learning_practice/homework/hw1",
    "array": "0-160",
    "conda_environment": "tf",
    "python_script": "hw1_base.py",
    "python_script_arguments": "--hidden 1000 --activation_out linear --epochs 1000 --results_path ./results/r1 --exp_index $SLURM_ARRAY_TASK_ID --output_type ddtheta --predict_dim 0"
  }
}
```

This script is running on **Slurm**, a workload manager that is used to manage resources on a computer cluster. The script requests various resources, including a specific partition, number of tasks, memory, output and error file locations, execution time, job name, email notifications, a working directory, and an array of tasks to execute. It also sets up a conda environment named "tf" and runs a Python script called "hw1_base.py" with specific arguments.
